  NULL,
  10,
  NULL,
  NULL,
  'Stable, Least Concern',
  NULL,
  '{"other_names": "Cape John Dory", "meristics": "Dorsal spines: 9-10; Dorsal soft rays: 22-24; Anal spines: 4; Anal soft rays: 20-22. Silvery grey in colour; indistinct dusky spot on or above lateral line and below front of soft dorsal fin.", "appearance": "The Cape Dory has a widespread geographic and depth (35-400 m) distribution and has been reported as common around Namibia and South Africa and the Western Indian Ocean. This species is commercially harvested as a food source and is also taken as bycatch by the hake fisheries. Although no species-specific catch statistics are available, fishing pressure is not thought to represent a major threat to this species at present.", "biology": "Max length: 90.0 cm TL.", "citation": "FishBase, The IUCN Red List of Threatened Species, Wikipedia"}',
  NULL
);

