  'Unknown, Data Deficient',
  NULL,
  '{"other_names": "Bartail Flathead, River Gurnard, Balkstert-platkop", "meristics": "Dorsal spines: 9-10; Dorsal soft rays: 13; Anal spines: 0; Anal soft rays: 13.", "appearance": "Brownish or grayish above, whitish below; caudal fin 2-3 horizontal black stripes. Head strongly depressed. Preopercular spines 2 - lower usually longest. It is identified by the distinctive colour pattern on the caudal fin: centrally yellow and black stripes on upper and lower margins.", "about": "The Bartailed Flathead are found widespread mainly tropical Indo-West Pacific species extending southwards to Mossel Bay. It has migrated through the Suez Canal into the Mediterranean. The ORI Tagging Project reveals a mean distance moved of 4km which suggests a degree of residency. However, adults are thought to migrate out of estuaries into the marine environment in order to spawn. Adults are found in estuaries and inshore coastal waters down to 15 m, found over sandy or muddy substrata, usually solitary. Juveniles make extensive use of mangrove estuaries but are classified as partially estuarine dependent as juveniles <10 cm SL are usually rare in estuaries. Adults are ambush predators feeding on shrimps, prawns, crabs, polychaete worms and small fishes. The juvenile\u2019s diet is unknown. Although it comprises a small component of catches, Bartailed Fathead is an important predator in shallow marine and estuarine environments. Small numbers are also caught in the illegal gill-net fishery in St Lucia, Vetch\u2019s Pier beach-seine fishery and the Kosi Bay trap fishery.", "biology": "Reproductive style: Unknown. Breeding/spawning season: Jul-Nov in KZN. Breeding/spawning locality: In the marine environment in the vicinity of KZN estuaries. Age at maturity: Unknown. Length at maturity: Combined sexes: 40 cm TL. Maximum recorded age: 7 years. Maximum recorded weight: 3.7 kg (IGFA 2012), 3.21 kg (SAUFF). Maximum recorded length: 100 cm TL.", "citation": "BQ Mann, R Kyle In: Mann BQ. (Ed). Southern African Marine Linefish Species Profiles. Special Publication, Oceanographic Research Institute, Durban 9: 179-180, FishBase"}',
  '[{"measure": "TL", "reference": "Visboekie", "coefficient": 0.0003019, "exponent": 2.383, "formula_type": "power-mm", "result_unit": "g"}]'
);

