  '{"other_names": "", "meristics": "Dorsal spines: 9; Dorsal soft rays: 11; Anal spines: 0; Anal soft rays: 11.", "appearance": "Brownish with small dark spots on upper body; usually with 4-5 dark brown bands crosses back; spiny dorsal with broad black band near edge and small black spots below, other fins darkly spotted.", "about": "Found in the Indo-West Pacific: Red Sea and East Africa to the Solomon Islands, north to southern Japan, and south to Australia. It occurs from near shore to 100 m (and up to 300 m) depth, on sand or mud bottoms. Larvae and juveniles rarely enter mangrove areas, especially the lower reaches.", "biology": "Max length: 50.0 cm TL; Common length: 40.0 cm TL.", "citation": "FishBase, The IUCN Red List of Threatened Species"}',
