  '{"other_names": "Blackblotch Flathead", "meristics": "Dorsal spines: 9; Dorsal soft rays: 12; Anal spines: 0; Anal soft rays: 12-13.", "appearance": "Brownish in colour, with 4-5 bands crossing back; spiny dorsal dusky brown, other fins are dark spotted; under opercle flap dark purple with light lines.", "about": "It is found in the western Indian Ocean from Delagoa Bay near the South African border to Karachi and through Red Sea to the eastern Mediterranean This species is data poor and little else is known about the diet, reproductive activities, fecundity or other ecological aspects for this species.", "biology": "It is known to grow to a maximum of 22 cm.", "citation": "FishBase, The IUCN Red List of Threatened Species"}',
