  '{"other_names": "Long-spine Glassy", "meristics": "Dorsal spines: 8; Dorsal soft rays: 9-10; Anal spines: 3; Anal soft rays: 9-11.", "appearance": "It has a single supraorbital spine; rostral spine absent and a preopercle ridge and rear margin serrated.  The interopercle edges are smooth except for few small serrae at angle. Cheek scales, 2-3 rows. Predorsal scales 13-18. Lateral line is continuous.", "about": "The Longspine Glassy can be found from South Africa to Kenya, Madagascar, R\u00e9union and Mauritius. It prefers estuarine environments, but it may enter freshwater systems. It is mainly found in ascending rivers and brackish water lakes. It feeds at night on crustaceans, fish fry and larvae and insects.", "biology": "Max length: 15.0 cm TL.", "citation": "FishBase, The IUCN Red List of Threatened Species"}',
