  '{"other_names": "Rosy Goatfish", "meristics": "Dorsal spines: 8 - 9; Dorsal soft rays: 8; Anal spines: 1; Anal soft rays: 6.", "appearance": "Colour variable; with or without a black saddle on caudal peduncle.", "about": "This species is widely distributed in the Indo-West Pacific: Red Sea and Persian Gulf south to South Africa reaching Struisbaai and east to the western Pacific. It is a near-shore demersal species occuring over soft bottoms in coastal areas near beaches, seagrass beds and reefs and murky areas of coastal waters.  It is often found solitarily but occasionally occurs in pairs.", "biology": "Max length: 43.0 cm TL; Common length: 23.0 cm TL.", "citation": "FishBase, The IUCN Red List of Threatened Species"}',
