  'Sea basses: Groupers and Rockcods',
  NULL,
  NULL,
  10,
  NULL,
  NULL,
  'Unknown, Data Deficient',
  NULL,
  '{"other_names": "Whiteblotched Koester", "meristics": "Dorsal spines: 7; Dorsal soft rays: 14-16; Anal spines: 3; Anal soft rays: 7.", "appearance": "This species is characterized by the following: Caudal, anal, and pelvic fins are pale (fin rays mostly reddish orange in life); a large oval, blackish brown blotch (most prominent dark mark on the head) covers most of the opercle.", "about": "The Scalyjay Koester is endemic and distributed in the Western Indian Ocean only along the coasts of South Africa in a depth range between 23-140 m.", "biology": "There is very little information on the life history and ecology of this marine species. Max length: 14.0 cm SL.", "citation": "FishBase, The IUCN Red List of Threatened Species"}',
