  'Unknown, Least Concern',
  NULL,
  '{"other_names": "", "meristics": "Dorsal spines: 5; Dorsal soft rays: 8; Anal spines: 3; Anal soft rays: 9.", "appearance": "Scale margins dark; pelvic fins bright yellow or orange. This mullet is silvery gray being paler below. It has a yellow iris.", "about": "The Diamond Mullet has an Indo-West Pacific distribution which extends from the eastern coast of Africa, including Algoa Bay in South Africa, through Madagascar and the Mascarenes east to Tonga and Marquesas Islands in French Polynesia and south to northern Western Australia and the Gulf of Carpentaria in western Queensland. It has also been reported inland on the Zambezi. This species lives in both brackish and freshwater. Adult fish are found in estuaries, coastal waters and in some cases, ascending rivers into fresh wate. It is a tropical species that inhabits inshore marine habitats including estuaries. It also travel hundreds of kilometres up rivers.", "biology": "Max length: 75.0 cm TL; Common length: 35.0 cm TL.", "citation": "FishBase, Wikipedia"}',
