  'Belonidae',
  'Needlefishes',
  NULL,
  NULL,
  NULL,
  NULL,
  NULL,
  'Unknown, Least Concern',
  NULL,
  '{"other_names": "Barred Garfish, Flat Needlefish", "meristics": "Dorsal spines: 0; Dorsal soft rays: 23-26; Anal spines: 0; Anal soft rays: 24-28.", "appearance": "Dorsally, they are blueish, white ventrally, with dark blotches and 12-14 vertical bars in the middle of their bodies. Flat needlefish have elongated bodies; with scythe-shaped pectoral and anal fins. They also have a dark lobe on the posterior part of their dorsal fins.", "about": "It is an epipelagic species and has a worldwide distribution in tropical and warm temperate waters and inhabits neritic and oceanic waters but more often found near islands. Found in estuaries, and coastal rivers. Thet sometimes form large schools and feed mainly on small fishes. It is usually caught by casting or trolling surface or near-surface lures, sometimes with the help of artificial lights.", "biology": "Max length: 140 cm TL. Common length: 70.0 cm SL. Max published weight: 4.8 kg (MOZ).", "citation": "FishBase, The IUCN Red List of Threatened Species, Wikipedia"}',
