  NULL,
  '{"other_names": "Yellowfin Garfish, Banded Needlefish", "meristics": "Dorsal spines: 0; Dorsal soft rays: 17-21; Anal spines: 0; Anal soft rays: 23-25.", "appearance": "Laterally compressed; origin of dorsal fin over 7th-10th ray of anal fin; caudal peduncle without lateral keels; caudal fin emarginated; predorsal scales moderately small. Caudal fin sub truncate; a black bar on cheek between opercle and preopercle; greenish dorsally, grading to silvery white ventrally.", "about": "Indo-West Pacific: Somalia and Tanzania to Durban, South Africa east to Pakistan, India, Sri Lanka and southeast Asia to New Guinea, Australia, and the Philippines in a depth range of 0-3 m. It inhabits coastal areas and enters estuaries, where it feeds mainly on small fish.", "biology": "Max length: 100.0 cm TL. Common length: 35.0 cm OT.", "citation": "FishBase, The IUCN Red List of Threatened Species"}',
