  'Smooth Puffer',
  'Gladde Blaasop',
  'Puffer Smooth',
  NULL,
  'Tetraodontidae',
  'Puffers, Blaasops, Blowfishes',
  NULL,
  NULL,
  10,
  NULL,
  NULL,
  'Unknown, Least Concern',
  NULL,
  '{"other_names": "", "meristics": "Dorsal spines: 0; Dorsal soft rays: 12-14; Anal spines: 0; Anal soft rays: 10-12.", "appearance": "Dorsal part of body without prickles, belly covered with prickles. It is greenish or dark grey above, silvery white below. Distinguished from other Lagocephalus species by the black gill opening.", "about": "It is widely distributed in the Indo-West Pacific in warm shallow waters from South Africa, East Africa, Persian Gulf and Madagascar east to Philippines and New Guinea, north to central Japan, south to northern Australia and appears to be common in parts of its range. It inhabits the continental shelf, and is found at depths ranging from 10-200 m. It is poisonous to eat.", "biology": "It is oviparous (producing young by means of eggs which are hatched after they have been laid by the parent). Max length: 90.0 cm.", "citation": "FishBase.  The IUCN Red List of Threatened Species"}',
