  NULL,
  'Unknown, Least Concern',
  NULL,
  '{"other_names": "", "meristics": "Dorsal spines: 13-14; Dorsal soft rays: 15-16; Anal spines: 3; Anal soft rays: 7.", "appearance": "Body has 12 oblique alternating black bars, specimens up to 40 cm with orange bars present between black bars, these orange bars fade in larger specimens: lips orange or yellow in colour.", "about": "This species is distributed in the western Indian Ocean from South Africa (KwaZulu-Natal) to Somalia, including Madagascar, and Aldabra in the Seychelles. The depth range for this species is 5-50 m. It inhabits coastal, coral reefs typically in turbid waters. It often occurs in pairs. Larger adults of the species lie in coral crevices with protruding lips, mimicing orange sponge. It also inhabits mangrove areas. This species is taken in handline and spear fisheries.", "biology": "It is oviparous with distinct pairing during breeding. Max length: 90.0 cm TL.", "citation": "FishBase, The IUCN Red List of Threatened Species"}',
