  '{"other_names": "", "meristics": "Dorsal spines: 9; Dorsal soft rays: 19-21; Anal spines: 3; Anal soft rays: 15-17.", "appearance": "It is silvery brown; with dark crossbands that disappear with growth.", "about": "Spadefish is distributed in the Indian Ocean: from Algoa Bay, South Africa; to the Andaman and Nicobar Islands, including India and Sri Lanka. It is a tropical marine species associated with reefs in a depth range of 40-70 m. It feeds on rock and coral-dwelling organisms and is edible.", "biology": "Max length: 75.0 cm TL; Common length: 30.0 cm TL.", "citation": "FishBase"}',
