  '{"other_names": "", "meristics": "Dorsal spines: 11; Dorsal soft rays: 12-13; Anal spines: 3; Anal soft rays: 11-12.", "appearance": "The body is rosy, olive or bluish dorsally, silvery below, black blotch in axil of pectorals.", "about": "Windtoy occurs from Cape Town to KZN in South Africa; it has also been collected off central Mozambique. It is a rare pelagic species that has a depth range of 20-160 m and moves inshore during stormy weather.", "biology": "Max length: 38.0 cm TL.", "citation": "FishBase, The IUCN Red List of Threatened Species"}',
