  'Unknown, Least Concern',
  NULL,
  '{"other_names": "Re\u00ebnboog-lipvis", "meristics": "Dorsal spines: 9; Dorsal soft rays: 12-13; Anal spines: 3; Anal soft rays: 12.", "appearance": "Head orangey-yellow with greenish bands and a black spot behind eye; body brown, females with a red band on back.", "about": "This small species is found from the East African coast south to KZN, South Africa, also from Madagascar, Seychelles and Chagos Archipelago. It inhabits deeper reef slope rubble habitats in depths from 5-43 m. It is captured as bycatch for the aquarium trade.", "biology": "They are oviparous with distinct pairing during breeding. Max length: 11.5 cm TL.", "citation": "FishBase, The IUCN Red List of Threatened Species"}',
